# SEO and Content Quality

## Required Metadata

Every `page.tsx` must export a `metadata` object with:

```tsx
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "Unique Page Title | ETCC India",
  description: "Unique 150-160 char description with primary keyword.",
  alternates: { canonical: "https://www.etccindia.com/page-slug" },
  openGraph: {
    title: "...",
    description: "...",
    url: "https://www.etccindia.com/page-slug",
    siteName: "ETCC India",
    type: "website",
  },
};
```

Do not duplicate titles or descriptions across pages.

## JSON-LD Structured Data

Every page must include at minimum:

- `Organization` schema (company details)
- `BreadcrumbList` schema (navigation path)
- Product pages additionally need `Product` schema with specs

Render JSON-LD as a `<script type="application/ld+json">` tag in the server component `page.tsx`.

## Heading Hierarchy

- One `<h1>` per page — the page title.
- `<h2>` for major sections.
- `<h3>` for items within sections.
- Never skip levels. Never use headings for styling only.

## Content Quality

Include specific technical details: VA ratings, accuracy classes, temperature ranges, certifications. Avoid generic phrases ("world-class", "best-in-class") without substantiation. Keep `public/sitemap.xml` in sync when adding/removing pages.
